6. Stay informed & follow advice given by your healthcare provider  Be informed on latest developments about the virus & follow advice given by your national and local public health authority or your employer on how to protect yourself & others from the virus.  COVID-19.

5. If you have fever cough & difficulty breathing, seek medical care early  Why?¬†National & local authorities will have up to date information on situation in your area. Calling in advance will allow your health care provider to quickly direct you to the right health facility

4. Practice respiratory hygiene Make sure you & people around you follow good respiratory hygiene (cover your mouth & nose when you cough or sneeze)  Why?¬†Droplets spread virus. By following good respiratory hygiene you protect the people around you from the  virus

3. Avoid touching eyes, nose and mouth  Why?¬†Hands touch many surfaces and can pick up viruses. Once contaminated, hands can transfer the virus to your eyes, nose or mouth. From there, the virus can enter your body and can make you sick.

2. Maintain social distancing Maintain at least 1 metre (3 feet) distance b/w yourself & anyone who is coughing/sneezing.  Why?¬†When someone coughs/sneezes they spray small liquid droplets from their nose or mouth which may contain the virus, u can get infected if u breathe it

#CoronaAlert Listing below measures one can take to prevent catching the virus  1. Wash your hands frequently Regularly & thoroughly clean your hands with an alcohol-based hand rub or wash them with soap & water.  Why?¬†Washing your hands kills viruses that may be on your hands.
